ow warriors.  Does it not say in the EQ manual under the description for warriors, &quot;....an expert in armed combat in all of its forms...&quot;?  I have been sending feedback to VI over the piercing issue and asking them to remove the cap for the above reason.  I encourage you all to do the same. <p>Kroo be do be do</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mistwolfeq>MistwolfEQ</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.gaiahealing.com/everquest/DarkKnight.jpg " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/13/02 7:05:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4391.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.gaiahealing.com/everquest/DarkKnight.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Piercing?  Is it worth it?</span><hr size=1> Think they put that cap in there to not cheat out rogues.  Rogues are kings/queens of piercing and they wanted to make them best at it, no?<br>
